item.media:title: I don't have a creative title for this
item.media:description:
So I have been away for a long minute, dealing with the usual mess of depression and angst that comes with adulthood not being what you wish it could be or not even being able to make it better. 

Anywho, my mother bought me the big set of touch 3 alcohol markers and this is what came from playing around with them and honestly not really caring much about design. As always, I liked it better before I colored it but at least it doesn't look horrible in my opinion. Leaving you all with this I am hoping to get more active again as I continue to improve myself and hopefully one day find a meaning for my existence. 

I am now off to do the work of the college, wish me luck 

~<3

item.title: Abby and The Blankie
item.media:title: Abby and The Blankie
item.media:description:
This is Abby! I adore her to pieces!.
She was the first of the several cats, (and needed no invitation) to try out the crocheted "baby or kitten-sized" blanket that I commission from
KittySib for Christmas.
I had been dreaming of doing this with KittySib for a while, about a year.

Unfortunately my Chihuahua eats the stuffing out of the trim of the traditional-types of cat beds, among eating other cat toys despite the slew of his own doggie toys...
...so, I had been wondering if a blanket would work. KittySib is soooo talented. The great quality yarn is soft but strong. It is crocheted nice and tight, and the cats haven't even made a single pull. Of course I do trim their nails- and if you, a shelter, or a vet trims your cats nails, you really shouldn't have a problem. Of course it would be perfect for a baby, too.

When it came it was actually bigger than I realized it would be! It goes from my feet to my chest. It's quite long for a person, just not side to side- after all I didn't order one for a tall human.
If you are at least interested in taking a look at KittySib 's work, I do HIGHLY recommend it. Her skills are phenomenal and simply put, professional.

Please to get more light on Abby's face, I had to brighten the photo a bit, so the blanket colours look a little brighter than they really are. I feel that's only fair to mention. But click on it BIG to see KittySib 's true madskills!

www.deviantart.com/kittysib

 

Now, go feel free to see more, ask her more, and see what's current on her ETSY account!!!


~~~~~~~~~

I understand if you don't have time to comment, but thank you for any kind comments, too. It's important to know this NOW, as I may NOT be able to do individual thank-you's for 's, or in case I cannot respond to each comment, either. Thanks for understanding. And, if you just came to view, I appreciate that, too.
]
